Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Snort won't start

Check configuration syntax: sudo snort -T -c /etc/snort/snort.conf
Verify file permissions on rules directory
Ensure no duplicate SIDs in rules
Issue: No alerts generated

Verify Snort is monitoring correct interface
Check that custom rules are included in snort.conf
Ensure test traffic matches rule criteria (ports, protocols)
Use tcpdump to verify packets are being sent
Issue: Scapy permission errors

Run packet generation scripts with sudo
Verify network interface name is correct
Check firewall rules aren't blocking traffic
Issue: Alert file empty or not updating

Verify log directory exists and is writable
Check Snort is running with correct output options
Ensure sufficient disk space for logs
